 At the MCC level,
 we can assess the effect of T1 on outcomes at the MCC level.
 Because T1 is assigned downstream,
 we can also evaluate its upstream effects on farmers linked to those MCCs.
 In contrast,
 the farmer-level treatment T2 varies only within MCCs,
 so its effects can be identified exclusively from farmer-level outcomes.
