\begin_layout Standard
In response to the challenge of unobservable milk quality in the Ugandan dairy value chain,
 we designed a first socio-technical innovation bundle targeting Milk Collection Centers (MCCs).
 This bundle aims to enhance transparency,
 improve record-keeping,
 and empower both MCC managers and farmers by making milk quality measurable and visible.
 The bundle,
 developed after extensive consultations with stakeholders and implemented together with the DDA,
 consists of three key components:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
1.
 Milk Analyzer:
 A central component of the innovation bundle is the installation of milk analyzers at MCCs.
 These machines assesses milk quality based on a set of compositional parameters,
 such as butterfat content and solids-not-fat (SNF).
 Another important parameter is the amount of added water,
 providing a more accurate assessment of what MCC managers usually test using gravity based methods.
 The testing process is non-destructive and takes less than one minute per sample,
 enabling rapid and accurate quality evaluation of each delivery.
\begin_inset Foot
status collapsed

